data.name: CreateDBSQLScript
data.value: IF NOT EXISTS (SELECT name FROM master.dbo.sysdatabases WHERE name = N'<dbname/>') CREATE DATABASE [<dbname/>] CONTAINMENT = NONE ON PRIMARY ( NAME = N'test', FILENAME = N'<mdfpath/>' , SIZE = 4096KB , FILEGROWTH = 1024KB ) LOG ON ( NAME = N'test_log', FILENAME = N'<ldfpath/>' , SIZE = 1024KB , FILEGROWTH = 10%)

data.name: QueryBasicTraceSummary
data.value: SELECT * FROM (SELECT MIN(StartTime) as [Trace Start Time], MAX(CurrentTime) as [Trace End Time] FROM [Table]) aa, (SELECT COUNT(*)[Queries Started] FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 9) a, (SELECT COUNT(*)[Queries Completed] FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 10) b, (SELECT SUM(Duration)[Total Query Duration], AVG(Duration)[Average Query Duration] FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 10) e, (SELECT( (SELECT MAX(Duration) FROM (SELECT TOP 50 PERCENT Duration FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 10 AND Duration > 0 ORDER BY Duration) AS BottomHalf) + (SELECT MIN(Duration) FROM (SELECT TOP 50 PERCENT Duration FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 10 AND Duration > 0 ORDER BY Duration DESC) AS TopHalf) ) / 2 AS [Median Query Duration]) g, (SELECT COUNT(*)[Commands Started] FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 15) c, (SELECT COUNT(*)[Commands Completed] FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 16) d, (SELECT SUM(Duration) [Total Command Duration], AVG(Duration) [Average Command Duration] FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 16) f, (SELECT( (SELECT MAX(Duration) FROM (SELECT TOP 50 PERCENT Duration FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 16 AND Duration > 0 ORDER BY Duration) AS BottomHalf) + (SELECT MIN(Duration) FROM (SELECT TOP 50 PERCENT Duration FROM [Table] WHERE EventClass = 16 AND Duration > 0 ORDER BY Duration DESC) AS TopHalf) ) / 2 AS [Median Command Duration]) h

data.name: QueryLongestRunningCommands
data.value: SELECT TOP 100 * FROM ( SELECT Duration, CPUTime, CONVERT(NVARCHAR(MAX), StartTime, 21) StartTime, CONVERT(NVARCHAR(MAX), CurrentTime, 21) as EndTime, DatabaseName, CONVERT(NVARCHAR(MAX), TextData) TextData, ConnectionID, NTUserName, NTDomainName, ApplicationName, ClientProcessID, SPID, CONVERT(NVARCHAR(MAX), RequestParameters) RequestParameters, CONVERT(NVARCHAR(MAX), RequestProperties) RequestProperties, RowNumber FROM [Table_v] WHERE EventClass = 16 UNION SELECT a.[Time Captured in Trace] Duration, b.CPUTime, b.StartTime, 'Command incomplete' EndTime, b.DatabaseName, CONVERT(NVARCHAR(MAX), b.TextData) TextData, b.ConnectionID, b.NTUserName, b.NTDomainName, b.ApplicationName, b.ClientProcessID, b.SPID, CONVERT(NVARCHAR(MAX), b.RequestParameters) RequestParameters, CONVERT(NVARCHAR(MAX), b.RequestProperties) RequestProperties, b.RowNumber FROM ( SELECT MAX(RowNumber) RowNumber, DATEDIFF("ms", MAX(StartTime), ( SELECT MAX(CurrentTime) FROM [Table] ) )[Time Captured in Trace] FROM [Table_v] a WHERE EventClass IN(15, 16) AND NOT StartTime IS NULL GROUP BY a.StartTime, ConnectionID, TextData HAVING COUNT(*) = 1 ) a, [Table_v] b WHERE b.RowNumber = a.RowNumber AND b.EventClass <>16 ) r ORDER BY Duration DESC

data.name: QueryMostImpactfulQueriesCommands
data.value:
-- Returns a ranking of all queries and commands completed within the trace by the number of other queries and commands that overlap the original query or command in question. -- The highest ranked among these may be likely offending queries or commands that affected other queries or commands on the server.
select b.[Overlapping Query Count], a.RowNumber, EventClass, EventClassName, StartTime, CurrentTime EndTime, Duration, CPUTime, ConnectionID, NTUserName, NTDomainName, DatabaseName, TextData, ClientProcessID, ApplicationName from [Table_v] a, ( select count(*)[Overlapping Query Count], OriginalQueryConnection, OriginalQueryEndRow from ( select a.StartTime, a.CurrentTime EndTime, a.ConnectionID, b.RowNumber OriginalQueryEndRow, b.StartTime OriginalQueryStart, b.CurrentTime OriginalQueryEnd, b.ConnectionID OriginalQueryConnection from [Table] a, ( select RowNumber, ConnectionID, StartTime, CurrentTime from [Table] where eventclass in (10, 16) ) b where ( ( (a.StartTime >= b.StartTime and a.StartTime <= b.CurrentTime) or(a.CurrentTime <= b.CurrentTime and a.CurrentTime >= b.StartTime) or(a.StartTime <= b.StartTime and a.CurrentTime >= b.CurrentTime) ) and a.ConnectionID<> b.ConnectionID and a.EventClass in (9, 10, 15, 16) ) ) OverlappingQueries group by OriginalQueryConnection, OriginalQueryEndRow ) b where a.RowNumber = b.OriginalQueryEndRow union select b.[Overlapping Query Count], a.RowNumber, EventClass, EventClassName, StartTime, null EndTime, DATEDIFF("ms", a.StartTime, (SELECT MAX(CurrentTime) FROM [Table])) [Duration], CPUTime, ConnectionID, NTUserName, NTDomainName, DatabaseName, TextData, ClientProcessID, ApplicationName from [Table_v] a, ( select count(*)[Overlapping Query Count], OriginalQueryConnection, OriginalQueryEndRow from ( select a.StartTime, a.CurrentTime EndTime, a.ConnectionID, b.RowNumber OriginalQueryEndRow, b.StartTime OriginalQueryStart, b.CurrentTime OriginalQueryEnd, b.ConnectionID OriginalQueryConnection from [Table] a, ( SELECT b.RowNumber, b.ConnectionID, b.StartTime, null CurrentTime FROM ( SELECT MAX(RowNumber) RowNumber, DATEDIFF("ms", MAX(StartTime), ( SELECT MAX(CurrentTime) FROM [Table] ) )[Time Captured in Trace] FROM [Table_v] a WHERE EventClass IN(9, 10, 15, 16) AND NOT StartTime IS NULL GROUP BY a.StartTime, ConnectionID, TextData HAVING COUNT(*) = 1 ) a, [Table_v] b WHERE b.RowNumber = a.RowNumber AND b.EventClass NOT IN (10, 16) ) b where ( a.StartTime >= b.StartTime and a.ConnectionID<> b.ConnectionID and a.EventClass in (9, 10, 15, 16) ) ) OverlappingQueries group by OriginalQueryConnection, OriginalQueryEndRow ) b where a.RowNumber = b.OriginalQueryEndRow order by [Overlapping Query Count] DESC

data.name: QueryPossibleRunawaySessions
data.value:
-- These sessions were active when the trace started and never showed any begin or end events. -- This can indicate the sessions were already active and remained active without ever completing. -- If heavy load isn't otherwise detectable in a trace, check with users of possible runaway sessions.
select 'Existing Session' as EventClassName, StartTime, Duration as [Session Duration at TraceStart], ConnectionID, NTUserName, NTDomainName, DatabaseName, SPID, TextData as [Session Roles], ClientProcessID, ApplicationName, RequestProperties as [Session Properties] from [Table] where connectionid not in ( select connectionid from ( select connectionID, eventclass from [Table] group by connectionid, eventclass ) a where a.eventclass in (1, 2, 15, 16, 9, 10) and not ConnectionID is null ) and not databasename is null and eventclass = 42 order by rownumber
